caption: This place is cool, you can basically get every permutation of possible Mexican dish within reason: shrimp tacos, steak burrito, chicken quesadilla. Located in Northwestern Memorial Hospital, I enjoy going here after doctors appointments.

DISCLAIMER: I HAVE ONLY EATEN THE BURRITO BOWLS, CHIPS,GUAC,COOKIES and ICECREAM and can't speak of the tacos or burritos !!! I will be honest I am TOTALLY a CHIPOTLE person. And with fair evaluation I have eaten BURRITO BEACH a few times (4 to be exact) and the aroma wafting from the restaurant is far more appealing than the actual taste of the food.  I thought maybe its the time of day,, location  or just an off day. Each time I have gotten the burrito bowls and somehow the rice is ALWAYS undercooked in my opinion, it tastes like it has been precooked and plastic packaged, the meat and veggie flavors are understated and barely there unless you load up with salsa,onions, cilantro,or peppers to compensate which I don't have to do with my aforementioned favorite. I respect others may feel differently. However fairly there are some differences and offerings that Burrito Beach has that has me still patronizing them on occasion.The concretes ( ice crean) and the Carmel Pecan and Chocolate Chip cookies are WONDERFUL !!! And sorry Chipotle but Burrito Beach's GUAC is better to me only because they use pico in theirs so I get chunks of tomatoes, cilantro and onion. I think Burrito Beach works well for those who want to have healthier and possibly vegan options and want to indulge in other than "American fare" with a low commitment to experiencing too many flavors.

I didn't enjoy my visit this morning. I come to this location all the time! My experience has always been pleasant, until today. All of the staff this morning had attitudes. I get it, its early. No biggie, I still order. My food was burnt, as it was on the grill forever, while the staff gathered in the back eating breakfast while only the girl taking the orders was on the line..  I know they have a watch for portions, but the lady hardly put an steak on my quesadilla . When I inquired about how much for extra meat, another worker came up and chimed in that it was an appropriate serving for the quesadilla. As if to say,  I couldn't order extra meat.  I'm not exaggerating,  I could count how much meat she put on my Quesadilla, on 1 hand. The lady who chimed in then whispered something in Spanish to the cashier and went back to the back. There were no more potatoes for my sisters Burrito, so the server scrapped the bottom of the pan for about 3 burnt potatoes, instead of getting fresh potatoes from the grill.  This is bad customer service. We come here all the time! But today was a drag.

Burrito Beach is definitely doing it better than the national chains, but this location specifically I would consider the cream of the Burrito Beach crop. I work about 20 steps from the Ohio street location however I find myself always coming to this location if I'm not in a time crunch. This location is brand new so the decor is pretty modern and it has a nice ambience. Theres also a pretty large staff who are all helpful and things move quickly. The food is always consistent here and that is to be appreciated. I highly recommend their baja chicken! I will say that I tried a chocolate shake there once and it was pretty gross. It tasted like I was drinking a chocolate protein shake after a workout, not a delicious shake I'd expect from a place like an ice cream shop. :(  Adding in frozen treats was a nice compliment to the usual Burrito Beach fare, but I believe it has to be done better if they're going to continue doing it/implementing it in new locations.
